Ask HN: Share earnings of electric vehicles chargers: profitability?
text:
Hello everybody, I have a startup idea but I couldn't find any info about the (possible) profitability. The idea is pretty simple: the company decides where to build a charging station for electric vehicles and anyone can contribute to installation costs for a fraction of it (e.g. Joe pays 5% of total, Hannah 2%, etc.). We take care of the installation process and routine maintenance and we get a small percentage of earnings, for instance 8%, while the remaining 92% is going to be split proportionally among the "investors" of the crowdfunding campaign (so Joe will get 5% and Hannah 2%). I'm planning to use only 150+ kW DC chargers (ideally, they should be 300 kW to be future-proof).

Do you know what's the average margin per kWh of a charging station like that (it doesn't matter in Europe or America, I'm ready to move if necessary)?

PS: Any tips or suggestions are welcome.

If you are wondering, that 8% doesn't come from any calculation, it's just to explain better how it would work.

title: Ask HN: Share your list of free e-books that're readable on mobile phone display
text:
I am often travelling between cities and I like to read epub books on my mobile phone during the trips.

The problem is that this requires some research about what books to select, find or buy a suitable format that are readable on small screens.

In this thread, can we create a list of free e-books that are readable on small screens? A5/A6 size PDF files, .epub files, books made of collection of responsive HTML files, etc. are all good candidates. Books of all genres are welcome. Alternative reading material like papers (really hard to find ones that are readable on small screens), comics, etc. are also welcome.
